Name: gestational choriocarcinoma
Definition: A choriocarcicoma that develops in the presence of a preceding gestational event.

Name: obsolete fetal or neonatal hemorrhage
Definition: A choriocarcicoma that develops in the presence of a preceding gestational event.

Name: placental site trophoblastic tumor
Definition: A choriocarcinoma that is characterized by low beta-hCG levels and arises from neoplastic transformation of intermediate trophoblastic cells.

Name: obsolete Good Prognosis metastatic Gestational Trophoblastic tumor
Definition: A choriocarcinoma that is characterized by low beta-hCG levels and arises from neoplastic transformation of intermediate trophoblastic cells.

Name: non-gestational choriocarcinoma
Definition: A choriocarcicoma that develops in the absence of a preceding gestational event.

Name: choriocarcinoma of ovary
Definition: A malignant ovarian germ cell neoplasm that has_material_basis_in trophoblastic cells.

Name: choriocarcinoma of the testis
Definition: A choriocarcinoma that is located_in the testis.

Name: obsolete mediastinum choriocarcinoma
Definition: A choriocarcinoma that is located_in the testis.

Name: pediatric CNS choriocarcinoma
Definition: A choriocarcinoma characterized by extraembryonic differentiation along trophoblastic lines and high serum and CSF levels of HCG/_-HCG
Synonym: Choriocarcinoma of the pediatric central nervous system
